Preconditions:
The `maze` parameter must be a 2D character array representing the maze.
The `entrance` parameter must be an integer array representing the coordinates of the entrance in the maze.
The `maze` must have at least one exit.
The `maze` must have a valid entrance at the specified coordinates.
The `maze` must not be null.
The `entrance` array must not be null.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer representing the number of steps in the shortest path from the entrance to the nearest exit.
If no path exists from the entrance to any exit, the method should return -1.